31/03/2011
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- The opposition Vetevendosje Movement and non-parliamentary party Fryma e Re (FeR) joined forces into one political group Wednesday (March 30th).
Party leaders Albin Kurti and Shpend Ahmeti agreed.
"This unification makes us stronger than ever before on what we have always desired:
fundamental political, economic and social changes in Kosovo." Ahmeti said that developments since the December general elections required the parties striving for change to unify.
(TV 21, Kohavision, Indeksonline, Telegrafi - 30/03/11)
